race.comment: COLOURS OF AUTUMN (7) did a good job last start to finish third at Townsville over 1400m, beaten 1.3 lengths. Cherry-ripe now. Is going well this campaign, recording a win and two minor placings from four starts and should be in the finish. KICKAGOAL KENNY (5) settled towards the tail when resuming last start then wound up strongly to score by a nose over 1250m at this track. Record here is strong and rates among the leading chances. SAND 'N' POWER (3) is racing well, scoring two back at this circuit before finishing a nose from the winner in second last time over 1609m at Townsville. Worth another chance. IT'S BEEN A TREK (1) won at this venue two starts ago but was below his best at a more recent appearance, finishing sixth over 1400m at this course. Deserves another chance.
